modules.description: Handles reading and processing OCaml input lines, managing a buffer for phrase storage, and executing the toplevel loop. Processes strings and lists of strings, supporting interactive evaluation and initialization file loading. Executes commands in a continuous loop, facilitating dynamic code interaction.

Provides functions to interact with user input during compilation, including reading and writing values from the terminal. Works with primitive types such as integers, strings, and booleans. Enables dynamic value injection during build processes, such as prompting for a version number or configuration flag.

Manages interactive OCaml input by reading, buffering, and executing code lines, supporting both single commands and initialization files. Processes strings and lists of strings, maintaining a persistent evaluation state through a toplevel loop. Allows dynamic code execution, enabling real-time testing and modification of OCaml expressions. Supports command history and incremental evaluation for interactive development.
